President Donald Trump has sent a letter to the Chairman, Representative, and Senator, in accordance with section 303(a)(6)(A) of the Defense Production Act of 1950. The letter addresses a shortfall in the defense industrial base and outlines actions that the Department of Defense will take to rectify the issue. Specifically, the actions will target critical technology item shortfalls related to thin-wall castings for military applications. President Trump also includes his determination that these proposed initiatives are essential to national defense.